<br>
<br>
<u><span style="font-size:large;">Tavern Heroes Charter</span></u><br>
<br>
<u><span style="font-size:medium;">1). Philosophy</span></u><br>
<br>
- Our members are here to help all levels, classes and races. We are an equal oppurtinuity guild.<br>
- Our members are dedicated to friendship and the guild first, loot is just a bonus that happens sometimes and not our primary goal. <br>
- The guild only acts in the interest for the whole guild, something that is good for the guild will be good for all.<br>
<br>
<u><span style="font-size:medium;">2). Rules of Conduct</span></u><br>
<br>
Things NOT allowed in this guild.<br>
<br>
- Begging.  (If you beg, you won't be in our guild long.) This means inside or outside of our guild.<br>
- Kill/Camp Stealing <br>
- Ninja Looting <br>
- Use of the guild chat as an auction channel <br>
- Abuse of our members to obtain loot or power level another guild member <br>
- Insult and Harassment of other players <br>
- Inappropriate language on an everyday basis <br>
- Whining about loot, groups, or anything that is considered by our officers as petty.<br>
<br>
All of our members will respect:<br>
<br>
- Verant policy <br>
- KGC policy<br>
<br>
<u><span style="font-size:medium;">3). Raids</span></u><br>
<br>
- We will try to grow and learn strategies that will allow us to raid any target in the Everquest world. <br>
- Expect to fail on targets, but don’t forget to learn and analyze what happened or went wrong. <br>
- Raid Goal: 1 Red raid per month and can attempt to hold up to 1 raid every 2 weeks. <br>
- Raid Attendance: Real life comes first, but when you're online, the guild is your family. We help each other out and everyone is expected to contribute to the growth of the guild and its members. If you are online on a night a red raid is scheduled, you should be there. These events are almost always scheduled in advance. Please make an attempt to be there at the announced time so we can start promptly. <br>
<br>
<u><span style="font-size:medium;">4). Loot</span></u><br>
<br>
Our general loot rules are:<br>
<br>
<a href="http://pub64.ezboard.com/ftavernheroesfrm10.showMessage?topicID=21.topic" target="_new">Click here to check out our loot Policy.</a><br>
<br>
<u><span style="font-size:medium;">5). Guild Life</span></u><br>
<br>
We are all member of the same guild and there are reason why we joined:<br>
<br>
- Our members will always prefer to group with other members of our guild when possible rather than with someone else.<br>
- If you are online playing an alt or doing something else and the guild needs you, you will be asked to come and help the guild (Now there are limitations to this, no one will ask or beg a druid/wizard in the guild for daily teleports for example; however, on a night of a raid, we do ask that if a situation like this occurs that you help transport people to the raid destination if you are not attending- but you will not be forced too) <br>
- The guild chat is use for fun, jokes, question, raids and so. Swears is not allowed on a daily basis, if a guild member is excessively swearing he/she will be reprimanded. (see rules of conduct)<br>
- When a member needs to leave our fantasy EQ world for Real life reasons, etc... please post on the forum that you will be away from the game for a week or however long.<br>
<br>
<u><span style="font-size:medium;">6). Epics</span></u><br>
<br>
Our Epic officer will define an epic priority depending on:<br>
<br>
- Guild needs <br>
- Attendance to raids<br>
<br>
In cases of conflict the guild leader will decide what is the best answer to the issue considering the advice of all.<br>
<br>
- An epic priority list will be maintained and limit to 5 epics at a time. The list will always contain 5 names.<br>
<br>
We are not capable of doing all epics for the moment, but we can complete few ones like: Rogue, Monk, Druid, Ranger and Shaman. So we'll begin to make the ones we can do to be able then to do the others.<br>
<br>
As we can't do all epics at same time we'll do one at the time.<br>
<br>
<u><span style="font-size:medium;">7). Main and Alternates</span></u><br>
<br>
- Each member will need to choose a Main character in game <br>
- Each member will be allowed have their alternates join the guild only if they themselves are playing the alternate<br>
<br>
- Main characters should have “/roleplay off” - See section 9<br>
<br>
- During raids mains and alternate will lotto differently, main character will always have loot priority over an alternate <br>
- You will be able change main and alternate once every 6 months for loot purposes during raids, but you are all more then welcome to play an alternate character when you want <br>
- We consider that 1 toon level 60 will always be better then 3 toons levels 30.<br>
- We'll not do epics for alternates.<br>
<br>
<u><span style="font-size:medium;">8)  . Recruitment</span></u><br>
<br>
<a href="http://pub64.ezboard.com/ftavernheroesfrm7.showMessage?topicID=67.topic" target="_new">Click here to check out our Membership Policy</a><br>
<br>
Our family is very important to us, so we want to know all new recruits before making them full member of the guild. <br>
<br>
<u><span style="font-size:medium;">9). Guild Tag</span></u><br>
<br>
You are member of our guild and we want you to be proud of this so the rules are:<br>
<br>
Anonymous only if:<br>
<br>
- You are on a break time<br>
- You don’t play a lot<br>
- No one should be playing Anonymous really.<br>
<br>
Role-play only if:<br>
<br>
- A druid, shaman, wizard, or cleric (but if at all possible please don’t play in roleplay mode )<br>
- If your getting harrased. (Hence the classes above.)<br>
<br>
Normal when:<br>
<br>
- You are an active member of the guild <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub64.ezboard.com/btavernheroes.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aerynne>Aerynne</A> at: 11/24/03 3:35 pm<br></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub64.ezboard.com/ftavernheroesfrm10.showNextMessage?topicID=24.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub64.ezboard.com/ftavernheroesfrm10.emailToFriend?topicID=24.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub64.ezboard.com/ftavernheroesfrm10.threadControl?topicID=24.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/traditional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub64.ezboard.com/ftavernheroesfrm10.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=24.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub64.ezboard.com/ftavernheroesfrm10.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=24.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub64.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="tavernheroesfrm10">Guild News & Information<option value="tavernheroesfrm4">Public - General<option value="tavernheroesfrm7">Public - Membership Applic